title: Minority Report
overview: In a future where a special police unit is able to arrest murderers before they commit their crimes, an officer from that unit is himself accused of a future murder.

title: Cowboy Bebop: Tengoku no tobira
overview: A terrorist explosion releases a deadly virus on the masses, and it's up the bounty-hunting Bebop crew to catch the cold-blooded culprit.

title: Kôkaku Kidôtai
overview: A cyborg policewoman and her partner hunt a mysterious and powerful hacker called the Puppet Master.

title: Despicable Me
overview: When a criminal mastermind uses a trio of orphan girls as pawns for a grand scheme, he finds their love is profoundly changing him for the better.

title: Loving Vincent
overview: In a story depicted in oil painted animation, a young man comes to the last hometown of painter Vincent van Gogh (Robert Gulaczyk) to deliver the troubled artist's final letter and ends up investigating his final days there.

title: The Thin Man
overview: Former detective Nick Charles and his wealthy wife Nora investigate a murder case, mostly for the fun of it.

title: Batman: Mask of the Phantasm
overview: Batman is wrongly implicated in a series of murders of mob bosses actually done by a new vigilante assassin.

title: Papillon
overview: A man befriends a fellow criminal as the two of them begin serving their sentence on a dreadful prison island, which inspires the man to plot his escape.

title: Tôkyô goddofâzâzu
overview: On Christmas Eve, three homeless people living on the streets of Tokyo discover a newborn baby among the trash and set out to find its parents.

title: Män som hatar kvinnor
overview: A journalist is aided by a young female hacker in his search for the killer of a woman who has been dead for forty years.

title: Solaris
overview: A psychologist is sent to a station orbiting a distant planet in order to discover what has caused the crew to go insane.

title: Sanjuro
overview: A crafty samurai helps a young man and his fellow clansmen save his uncle, who has been framed and imprisoned by a corrupt superintendent.

title: Wreck-It Ralph
overview: A video game villain wants to be a hero and sets out to fulfill his dream, but his quest brings havoc to the whole arcade where he lives.

title: The Game
overview: After a wealthy banker is given an opportunity to participate in a mysterious game, his life is turned upside down when he becomes unable to distinguish between the game and reality.

title: Ratatouille
overview: A rat who can cook makes an unusual alliance with a young kitchen worker at a famous restaurant.

title: Chinatown
overview: A private detective hired to expose an adulterer finds himself caught up in a web of deceit, corruption, and murder.

title: Baby
overview: An elite counter-intelligence unit learns of a plot, masterminded by a maniacal madman. With the clock ticking, it's up to them to track the terrorists' international tentacles and prevent them from striking at the heart of India.

title: Abre los ojos
overview: A very handsome man finds the love of his life, but he suffers an accident and needs to have his face rebuilt by surgery after it is severely disfigured.

title: Psycho
overview: A Phoenix secretary embezzles $40,000 from her employer's client, goes on the run, and checks into a remote motel run by a young man under the domination of his mother.

title: Mou gaan dou
overview: A story between a mole in the police department and an undercover cop. Their objectives are the same: to find out who is the mole, and who is the cop.
stars: ['Alan Mak', 'Andy Lau', 'Tony Chiu-Wai Leung', 'Anthony Chau-Sang Wong']
